, acting like Governor Makinde’s ‘appendage’ and also his contractor. “Therefore, he has no moral preserve to be a peacemaker as peace can not be achieved when insincere people who are self-seekers sit at the table as peacemakers. “Most importantly, PDP was peaceful in the South-West before Prince Oyinlola returned from APC and committed and loyal leaders of the party in the zone will on their own, ensure that issues in the party are resolved.” Vanguard News Nigeria By James Ogunnaike A faction of the Ogun State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), loyal to late Senator Buruji Kashamu on Thursday said the former Governor of Ekiti State, Mr. Ayodele Fayose, lacked the moral right to complain about the leadership of the party in the South West.… September 10, 2020 In "Politics" Prince Olagunsoye Oyinlola, former governor of Osun state and some other members of the African Democratic Congress in South West have decamped to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). The defection took place on Wednesday during the South West Rally held at Mapo Hall in Ibadan. Some of the defectors were… March 18, 2020 In "Politics" The People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in Ogun State on Thursday cautioned the Oyo State Governor, Engr. Seyi Makinde to stop meddling into the affairs of the party in the state, but rather, he should find means of putting his ‘house’ in order. January 21, 2021 In "Politics"